1 B. When a second tie vote is certified in the nomination or
2 election of any candidate in any Runoff Primary, General Election or
3 any Primary Election, the election board which is authorized by law
4 to issue the certified list or certificate of election shall, at a
5 public meeting of the board and in the presence of the candidates
6 involved or their designee, if they or any of them desire to be
7 present, select the nominee or electee by lot.
8 B. C. When a nominee or electee is to be selected by lot
9 pursuant to the provisions of this section, the following procedures
10 shall be observed:
11 1. The secretary of the appropriate election board shall, on or
12 before the tenth day following the second election, notify each of
13 the tying candidates for which the vote was tied. The notice shall
14 include the time, date and location of the selection, shall be made
15 in writing by registered or certified mail and shall be postmarked
16 not fewer than five (5) days prior to the meeting;
17 2. A candidate may designate one person as a witness to attend
18 the meeting on the candidate's behalf. The designation shall be
19 made in writing, signed by the candidate and presented to the
20 secretary of the appropriate election board;
21 3. The secretary of the appropriate election board shall, in
22 full view of those present at the meeting, clearly write or print
23 the name of each tied candidate on separate pieces of paper
24 measuring approximately equal size. The names of the candidates
